Quick easy Turkey BLT lettuce wraps with avocado 🥑 and a soft boiled egg 🥚 for lunch today! I used thick sliced deli turkey and uncured pre-cooked bacon 🥓 from Trader Joe’s that I crisped up in the microwave for 30 seconds then placed in butter lettuce 🥬 leaves with tomato 🍅 slices and a little seasoned salt.
.Credit: @zestmylemon

🥚 For the jammy eggs, fill a pot with enough water to cover the eggs and bring to a full boil. Carefully place the eggs into the boiling water and boil for 8 minutes. Immediately remove the eggs to an ice bath and let cool in the cold water for 10 minutes before peeling.
.

I give you 3 ingredient cheese bread! (3 ingredients minus my seasonings lol) This was unbelievably delicious!!! 
Double taps if you love this!!!!

Think all the flavor of Little Caesar’s Italian cheesy bread but better because it has no carbs!!! My mom, my sister, and my best friend were blown away with how good this was!

You need 1 cup grated mozzarella cheese, 1 cup grated parmesan cheese, 1 egg and seasoning of choice. I used a ton of granulated garlic powder, and this garlic lover’s seasoning that grinds dried garlic and herbs.

In a bowl scramble your egg add your cheese, and however much seasoning you want. Spread into a circle (like pizza dough) on a parchment lined baking sheet, sprinkle with more seasoning and bake 350 10-25 minutes depending on your oven until browned, I broiled mine for a minute or so before taking it out! This was so good! I was worried about it being eggy but it wasn’t at all! The egg just acts as a binder keeping the cheeses together 💁🏻‍♀️
